        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 2:22PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 222 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Kibbee, or 7 miles
southeast of Soperton, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Vernon, Vidalia, Ailey, Higgston, Tarrytown, and Kibbee.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
